FBIS3-15721 "drsov046_a_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-046 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Kozyrev, Silajdzic Begin Talks LD0903105194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0946 GMT 9 Mar 94 LD0903105194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Vladimir Beskromnyy and Aleksandr Krylovich] [Text] Moscow, 9 Mar -- A wide range of issues relating to ways to settle the Bosnian crisis are being discussed by Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev and Haris Silajdzic, prime minister of Bosnia-Herzegovina. Their talks have just started in Moscow. The head of the Bosnian Government arrived here during the night from France, where he has been on a working visit. Mate Granic, Croatian deputy head of government and foreign minister, is expected in Moscow later today. Kozyrev is to give a news conference in the afternoon following his meetings with the Bosnian and Croatian representatives.
